long_desc.thetext:
In a wizard's performFinish() method, add a propertySet to IHost:

            IHost conn = 
            	sr.createHost(sysType, // ...
            	);
            IPropertySet ps = conn.createPropertySet("windriver");
            ps.addProperty("tc", "test");
            sr.saveHost(conn);

When a connection is created through that code, the property set is correctly persisted. 

But when I quit and re-start RSE, the property set is no longer accessible.
Looking at the files created by the Persistence Manager, I notice that the 
PS.myhost directory has now been moved from below the created system, to the generic properties.

This bug makes attaching PropertySets to an IHost impossible.
Workaround: Attach the PropertySet to a ConnectorService, this is persisted correctly.

Adjusting target milestone and priority due to bug 170932. Keeping severity "Normal", because there is a workaround (associate the PropertySet with a ConnectorService rather than the IHost).

According to bug 170932 comment 1, the fix should be easy:

RSEDOMImporter.java, line 131:

    restorePropertySet(profile, child);

_must_ be:

    restorePropertySet(host, child);

The bug is perhaps in AbstractConnectorService line 446:

    // Check the saved passwords if we still haven't found a good password.
    if (passwordInformation == null && userId != null && !forcePrompt) {

should be

    if (passwordInformation == null && userId != null) {

because password info needs to be retrieved even is prompting is forced -- the prompt should show the persisted password.

