I think you can already achieve that using the IActionRenderer interface with the following implementation to display the category value for instance (see below). But you could potentially display anything at all in the tooltip. There is a getUserValue(String) in DataPointHints you can use together with a second DataSet in the Series. It will retrieve the DataSet with the id specified and evaluate the current row for this DataSet. This is actually how it works in BIRT reports where it's possible to have tooltip expressions.

public void processAction( Action action, StructureSource source )
{
	if ( ActionType.SHOW_TOOLTIP_LITERAL.equals( action.getType( ) ) )
	{
		TooltipValue tv = (TooltipValue) action.getValue( );
		if ( StructureType.SERIES_DATA_POINT.equals( source.getType( ) ) )
		{
			final DataPointHints dph = (DataPointHints) source.getSource( );
			tv.setText( ChartUtil.stringValue( dph.getBaseValue() ) );
		}
	}

